# LiberFi SDK Source Location

The source code for liberfi.io related components (React SDK) is located at `../react-sdk` relative to this project.

When investigating or modifying liberfi.io component internals, look for the corresponding source files under the `../react-sdk` directory.

# LiberFi SDK Version Check Rules

When checking the latest version of `@liberfi.io/*` packages, follow this priority order:

1. **Local source code first**: Read `../react-sdk/packages/*/package.json` to get the `version` field. This is the most up-to-date source of truth during active development.
2. **npm registry fallback**: If the local source is unavailable or you need to verify the published version, run `npm view @liberfi.io/<package-name> version` (ensure registry is set to the official npm source first).

# LiberFi SDK Version Update Rules

When updating `@liberfi.io/*` SDK versions in `apps/web/package.json`, you MUST also update the corresponding `peerDependencies` and `devDependencies` in all workspace packages under `packages/`. Specifically:

1. Search all `packages/*/package.json` for any `@liberfi.io/*` references in both `peerDependencies` and `devDependencies`.
2. Update `peerDependencies` versions (using `>=` range) to match the new SDK version.
3. Update `devDependencies` versions (using `^` range) to match the new SDK version.
4. **Sync `@chainstream-io/sdk` version**: Check the `@chainstream-io/sdk` version used by `@liberfi.io/client` (inspect its `package.json` in `node_modules/@liberfi.io/client/package.json`), then update `@chainstream-io/sdk` in all `apps/*/package.json` and `packages/*/package.json` that reference it to match that version.
5. After all `package.json` files are updated, **stop and tell the user** to run the following commands themselves:
   ```bash
   nrm use npm   # switch to official registry
   pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile
   pnpm build
   nrm use taobao  # switch back to mirror
   ```
   Do NOT run `pnpm install` or `pnpm build` automatically.
